Package nodes

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ASTNode
    An interface used for every node inside the abstract syntax tree.
    MathNode
    An interface used by expression-specific nodes inside the abstract syntax tree.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ActNode
    A class that represents a node used for act nodes inside the abstract syntax tree.
    AssignmentNode
    A class that represents a node used for assignment operations between variables or expressions/constants.
    ConstantNode
    A class that represents a constant node inside the AST and that is used for arithmetical or assignment operations.
    CubeNode
    A class that represents a cube node and it is used for a specific operation, namely the calculation of the power of three of a specific number.
    DifferenceNode
    A class that represents a difference node and it is used for a specific operation, namely the difference between the values of its respective sons.
    LvalNode
    A class that represents a left node(with respect to the assignment node).
    OutputNode
    A class that represents an output node.
    ProductNode
    A class that represents the product between the values of two variables.
    ProgramNode
    A class that represents a node used for the beginning of the abstract syntax tree.
    QuotientNode
    A class that represents the division of the values of two variables (characters).
    RValNode
    A class that represents a right node(with respect to the assignment node).
    SceneNode
    A class that represents a node used for scene nodes inside the abstract syntax tree.
    SquareNode
    A class that represents a square node and it is used for a specific operation, namely the calculation of the power of two of a specific number.
    SumNode
    A class that represents a sum node and it is used for a specific operation, namely the sum between the values of its respective sons.
